      "type": "teach",
      "title": "The naming dot",
      "body": "Shavian has no capital letters at all — so how do you spell a name? With a small dot right before the word: ·Sam, ·Ann, ·London. The dot is the only clue that a word is a proper name — a person or a place."
    },
